# Worklog Discipline

When making meaningful project changes, update `WORKLOG.md` before final handoff.

## Update Required For

- Behavior changes (routes, UI flow, runtime behavior)
- Architecture or implementation pattern changes
- Process/governance changes (SOPs, policies, rules)

## Entry Expectations

- Read the latest entry number before adding a new entry
- Add new entries at the top (reverse chronological)
- Include: Goal, Changes, Notes/decisions, Follow-ups
- Use real file paths in `Changes`
- Keep one entry per logical unit of work

## Do Not Skip

If meaningful code/process changed and worklog is stale, stop and add the entry before concluding work.
